---
import { Picture } from "@astrojs/image/components";
import hsf1 from "~/assets/hsf-people.png";
const widths = [450, 800, 1200];
const sizes = "(min-width: 1024px) 37vw, 85vw";
---

<div
	id="about"
	class="flex flex-col lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-4 md:gap-8 h-full w-full py-24 justify-content-center items-center"
>
	<div
		class="mx-8 lg:ml-32 px-8 lg:mx-0 flex gap-4 flex-col bg-semitransparent rounded-2xl"
	>
		<span
			class="pt-6 text-md xs:text-xl xl:text-3xl font-semibold font-heading"
		>
			<span class="border-b-8 border-b-primary">More</span> than a CTF
		</span>
		<p class="text-xs xs:text-md 2xl:text-lg font-light pb-8 xs:pb-0">
			CTFs are awesome for honing your cyber skills, but let's face it: they're
			not always a true reflection of real-life challenges. It's time to change
			that.
		</p>
		<p class="hidden xs:block text-xs xs:text-md 2xl:text-lg font-light">
			MCPS HSF is designed to be more realistic, with the winning teams chosen
			based on their score and writeup. We want to see <span
				class="text-primary font-normal">how you think</span
			>, not just how fast you can solve a problem.
		</p>
		<p class="hidden xs:block text-xs xs:text-md 2xl:text-lg font-light pb-8">
			And fun? We've got that covered too! Each year's competition revolves
			around a <span class="text-primary font-normal">mystery</span> and there's
			always at least one physical challenge (last year it was lockpicking).
		</p>
	</div>
	<Picture
		class="rounded-2xl"
		src={hsf1}
		sizes={sizes}
		widths={widths}
		alt="HSF People"
	/>
</div>

<style>
	#about {
		background-image: radial-gradient(theme("colors.text") 1%, transparent 2%),
			radial-gradient(theme("colors.text") 1%, transparent 2%);
		background-position: 0 0, 50px 50px;
		background-size: 100px 100px;
	}
</style>
